PN,39707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F397A1778785872
OL,3,CSir Paul McCartney describes how songs
OL,4,Ccan unite people on political spectrum
OL,6,F"My dad played the piano at home.
OL,7,FThere were a lot of jokes. And so they
OL,8,Fkept their heads above water by
OL,9,Flaughing at the whole thing. And I
OL,10,Fthink that was something that found
OL,11,Fits way into The Beatles.
OL,13,F"I think it gave us a good sense of
OL,14,Fhumour ` that no matter what we were
OL,15,Fgoing to do, like arrive in America
OL,16,Fand have the New York press ready to
OL,17,Fmake fun of us, we gave as good as we
OL,18,Fgot."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUzD@EO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/7
